<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1922-11-01T02:34:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1922-11-01T02:34:00-05:00" n="769" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d769">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">861.77/2799: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The President of the Technical Board</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Stevens</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Harbin</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-11-01T16:00:00+08:26"><hi rend="italic">November 1,
                                        1922—4 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received November 2—12:04
                                a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Your October 27, 4 p.m. through Peking. Final meeting this day abolished
                            Technical Board and all matters will be completed as soon as possible.
                            Since October 15th we have had no direct communication with Vladivostok
                            which is delaying settlement of details. Inter-Allied committee
                            dissolved itself October 24th. Copy furnished Peking.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Stevens</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>